  • Field Details

    • addressEntryList

      private final java.util.TreeMap<java.lang.String,​java.util.TreeSet<AddressEntry>> addressEntryList
      the data structures that will hold the data for the address book. Composed of a TreeMap where the key is a String(the last name of the AddressEntry and the value is the a TreeSet AddressEntry. This is because java does not contain a multiset in standard libraries. Tree is used instead of hash because tree preserves the natural ordering of key which makes printing in sorted order by last name(key) easy.
